name: AI Resume Twin
description: AI Chatbot acts as a candidate's digital twin, allowing recruiters natural language access to experience. It's a Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) system using LlamaIndex and local Ollama. Llama 3 handles conversation, while all minilm embeds JSON resume data into a searchable vector store. Prompt Engineering ensures answers are grounded solely in the resume, providing accurate, direct evaluation.

name: Multi-class depression detection
description: Developed an NLP-based system using BERT to classify text into depression levels (Not, Moderate, High). Implemented data preprocessing, class imbalance handling, and model fine-tuning with TensorFlow and HuggingFace Transformers. Evaluated performance using Scikit-learn metrics and visualizations, with deployment-ready saved model weights.

name: Dog and Cat - CNN Image Classification
description: This project uses a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) built with TensorFlow and Keras to classify images of dogs and cats. The data is preprocessed, organized, and split into training and validation sets. The model, trained with convolutional and dense layers, is evaluated using accuracy, loss curves, and a confusion matrix to measure performance..

name: Dynamic Attendance Manager
description: A web-based attendance management system built with React, Redux, Redux-Saga, HTML, and CSS. The system allows admins to efficiently manage and update attendance records, while students can securely view their own attendance. Role-based access control ensures proper authorization, providing a structured, user-friendly, and responsive interface for smooth attendance tracking.

name: Ultrasonic Radar
description: Ultrasonic Radar interfaced with Arduino Uno Board and output visualization using Processing IDE
